title: ‘Dhurandhar’ beats ‘Baahubali 2’ to record the highest 3rd Saturday collection

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A global review reveals significant inconsistencies in omega-3 fatty acid recommendations worldwide, leaving many individuals short of essential nutrients for lifelong wellness. While the importance of DHA and EPA is recognized, guidelines vary widely, impacting intake targets for adults, teens, and special populations like pregnant women.
title: How much Omega-3 do you really need each day? A new global review breaks it down

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Hundreds of Indian H-1B visa holders are stranded in India after US consulates abruptly canceled their work permit renewal appointments, rescheduling them months later. This disruption follows the Trump administration's expanded social media vetting policy, leaving highly skilled workers facing job uncertainty and significant delays in returning to the US.
title: ‘Stuck in India’: US cancels H-1b interviews, leaving workers stranded back home

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: American embassies worldwide, including in India, are facing up to a year-long wait for visa appointments due to enhanced screening. Tech giants like Google and Apple are now cautioning H-1B visa holders against international travel, fearing extended stays abroad. New social media checks are causing significant backlogs, impacting professionals and their families.
title: US department of state gives update on the delay in Visa appointments

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Bangladesh unrest: Mob torches BNP leader’s house; 7-year-old daughter burnt to death

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill's T20 World Cup 2026 squad omission is seen as a strategic correction, not a snub. Experts suggest selectors are prioritizing defined roles and recent T20 form over past Test heroics. This shift emphasizes specialists for specific game phases, reflecting a pragmatic approach to team composition for the tournament.
title: Ex-India cricketer calls Gill snub 'damage control'; says selectors 'got carried away'

author: SACHIN SHARMA
description: A 17-year-old girl allegedly orchestrated her father's murder with her lover after he persistently opposed their relationship and confined her. The girl, who had previously attempted to sedate her parents, succeeded on December 18, allowing her boyfriend and his accomplice to fatally stab her father.
title: Man opposes daughter’s relationship, 17-yr-old sedates parents, gets father killed by boyfriend

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: In a recent update following a serious car crash, Nora Fatehi shared that she is safe and sound despite enduring minor injuries and a concussion. The incident, triggered by a reckless drunk driver, left her rattled and thrown about in her car.
title: Nora Fatehi opens up about car crash: 'Saw my life flash before my eyes'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Former Pakistani Prime Minister Imran Khan and his wife Bushra Bibi received a 17-year prison sentence in the Toshakhana-II corruption case. Khan, through his legal team, has called for nationwide protests and plans to challenge the conviction, alleging the verdict was delivered hastily and without evidence.
title: ‘Prepare for street movement’: Imran Khan calls for protests after 17 yrs sentence

author: TOI Education
description: The Supreme Court has regularised Bachelor of Dental Surgery degrees for students admitted to Rajasthan private dental colleges with relaxed NEET criteria. The court held colleges and the state government accountable for violating admission rules. Affected students will provide pro-bono services. Private colleges must deposit Rs 10 crore each, and the Rajasthan government Rs 10 lakh.
title: SC regularises BDS degrees of Rajasthan students; private dental colleges penalised

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US companies are grappling with significant disruptions as tighter social media checks by the Trump administration have led to prolonged visa stamping delays for Indian professionals. Many H-1B visa holders are stranded in India, forcing employers to explore remote work options or expedite travel back to the US to avoid visa expiry.
title: US visa delays: Indian H-1B workers stranded as Trump admin starts social media checks

author: TNN
description: A video shows BJP MLA Parag Shah slapping a rickshaw driver in Ghatkopar East. The MLA stated the driver was violating traffic rules and residents had complained about such incidents. The incident occurred during a protest against traffic violations. Police are investigating the matter. The opposition criticized the MLA's actions.
title: Watch: Mumbai BJP MLA slaps auto-rickshaw driver; Congress hits out

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Patrick Mahomes’ season-ending knee injury has left the Chiefs in unfamiliar territory. While Brittany Mahomes has remained silent, his mother Randi publicly thanked fans for their prayers and support. As Mahomes begins a lengthy rehabilitation, the Chiefs face a rare playoff miss but remain optimistic about his full recovery and return in 2026.
title: Brittany Mahomes silent as Randi shares hope amid Patrick Mahomes recovery

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US job growth is significantly slowing, with hiring at its weakest in two decades. While the economy isn't contracting, this trend, fueled by retirements and immigration restrictions, suggests a stable but uneven labor market. Experts warn of a potential K-shaped recovery, benefiting the wealthy while straining others, with AI adding further uncertainty.
title: After rising costs, America faces its next hurdle — a ‘stagnating’ job market

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: The Telangana government is taking over Phase-I of the Hyderabad Metro Rail from Larsen & Toubro for Rs 2,000 crore, aiming to improve public transport and bridge the city's socio-economic divide. This move is part of a larger plan to expand the Metro network, with Phase-II proposals submitted to the Centre for funding and approval.
title: From heritage lanes to high-tech hubs: How Hyderabad Metro is changing the city

author: ARANI BASU
description: Shubman Gill's injury opened the door for Sanju Samson, but sources reveal the team management had already planned to replace Gill at the top due to a lack of runs. This move signals a shift in strategy for the T20 World Cup, with the team management moving on from Gill as the all-format leader.
title: How BCCI’s 'Project Shubman Gill' collapsed: Inside the shocking T20 World Cup omission

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: South Africa shooting: 10 killed as gunmen open fire; probe under way

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Lamarr Wilson, a well known Los Angeles based tech and lifestyle YouTuber with over 2.11 million subscribers, has died by suicide at 48. His death was confirmed by the Los Angeles County Medical Examiner and a family member. Tributes from Geoff Keighley and fans highlight Wilson’s lasting impact on the tech and creator community.
title: Why did Lamarr Wilson commit suicide? Inside the heartbreaking loss

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Ten individuals have been apprehended in Bangladesh following the brutal murder of Dipu Chandra Das, a Hindu garment worker. Das was allegedly beaten to death by a mob on December 18 over blasphemy accusations, with his body subsequently set ablaze. Authorities are under pressure to address mob violence amid broader unrest.
title: Yunus says RAB, police probing Hindu man's murder in Bangladesh; 10 arrested

author: AFP
description: A former culture ministry HR manager, Christian Negre, allegedly drugged around 200 women with diuretics during job interviews, forcing them into humiliating situations. Hiyam Zarouri recounts being made to walk for hours in pain after her coffee was spiked. Negre admitted to imposing humiliating situations and was fired, but victims fear he still poses a threat.
title: French culture boss accused of mass 'drinks spiking' to humiliate women

author: TNN
description: Event organizer Satadru Dutta was arrested following chaos during the Messi tour in Kolkata. Police seized Rs 22 crore from his accounts, suspecting black money use. Dutta claimed Rs 100 crore was spent, but investigators doubt his financial figures. He also blamed others for the event's disorder, citing pressures for increased access.
title: Messi got Rs 89cr for India tour, govt Rs 11cr as tax: Organiser blames ‘influential' people

author: AYANTIKA PAL
description: Young patients are increasingly using social media-derived psychological terms in therapy, presenting a new challenge for clinicians. While this vocabulary aids expression, it also leads to self-diagnosis and over-pathologizing normal experiences. Therapists are adapting to bridge this linguistic gap, validating feelings while reframing them accurately.
title: Can I lore drop? How Gen Z language is changing mental therapy, one word at a time

author: NITHYA MANDYAM
description: Karnataka is experiencing a significant cold spell as winter tightens its grip, with dense morning fog disrupting travel. Minimum temperatures have dipped 2-3°C below normal across the state, with north-interior districts like Bidar recording the lowest at 5.3°C. The chill is expected to persist through the month-end.
title: 8.5°C in Bengaluru Urban dist? Cold wave and fog tighten their grip in festive season; holiday travel disrupted

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill's surprising omission from the 2026 T20 World Cup squad has ignited debate, signaling a shift in India's T20 strategy. Sanju Samson is poised to open, with Ishan Kishan returning as a second wicketkeeper. Rinku Singh secures a finisher's role, highlighting a focus on aggressive starts and defined player roles for the upcoming tournament.
title: 'Gill’s exit was inevitable': Ashwin drops blunt truth on T20 World Cup snub

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Three men of Indian origin have received prison sentences for their involvement in a violent clash at a Kabbadi tournament in Alvaston. Boota Singh, Damanjit Singh, and Rajvinder Takhar Singh were convicted of violent disorder and weapon possession.
title: Gunshot, knives: 3 Indian-origin men arrested in UK for violence in kabaddi match

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Bollywood actress Nora Fatehi sustained minor injuries after a drunk driver crashed into her car in Mumbai. Despite the collision, she proceeded with her scheduled performance at the Sunburn music festival. Fatehi later shared her experience on Instagram, emphasizing the dangers of drinking and driving.
title: 'Traumatic': Nora Fatehi after drunk driver rams into her car; recounts horrific accident

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Google and Apple have advised US-based employees on work visas against international travel due to potential 12-month delays at US embassies. This follows warnings from outside counsel about significant visa stamping appointment backlogs. The delays are attributed to new social media screening requirements for visa applicants.
title: US immigration crackdown: Google and Apple warn visa workers; firms say 'don't travel.'

author: TNN
description: A racket charging relatives for legally free inmate meetings at Tihar Jail has been exposed. An inmate's tip-off led to an investigation where undercover officials were asked for money. As a precaution, 20-25 data entry operators were transferred while the probe into touts and system misuse continues. Biometric authentication is being introduced to enhance security.
title: Pay to meet Tihar inmates: Operators' role under lens over illegal mulakat charges

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi grappled with severe smog on Sunday, triggering stringent anti-pollution measures and widespread air travel chaos. Authorities activated Stage-IV of GRAP as Air Quality Index levels soared into 'very poor' and 'severe' categories. Over 500 flights faced delays and 138 were cancelled due to drastically reduced visibility, impacting thousands of passengers.
title: Delhi chokes under thick smog: AQI hits ‘severe’ in some areas; flights, train services hit

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The squad was announced on Saturday by BCCI secretary Devajit Saikia, captain Suryakumar Yadav and chief selector Ajit Agarkar. Axar Patel was named vice-captain. Ishan Kishan returned to the T20I side after leading Jharkhand to the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy title, while Rinku Singh was also recalled after missing the recent 3-1 series win in South Africa.
title: 'Didn’t see it coming': Former cricketer flags 'lacking clarity' after Gill, Jitesh dropped

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill's surprising omission from India's 2026 T20 World Cup squad and Axar Patel's appointment as vice-captain have sparked debate. Sunil Gavaskar expressed shock, highlighting Gill's class despite recent struggles and attributing his T20 rhythm issues to a layoff and natural game suited to longer formats. Gavaskar offered personal advice, believing Gill will return with renewed rhythm and fortune.
title: 'Ghar pe kisiko bolo nazar utar de': Gavaskar’s advice to Gill after T20 World Cup snub

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US Coast Guard, with Department of Defense backing, seized an oil tanker off Venezuela, citing its connection to sanctioned oil funding narco-terrorism. This follows a previous seizure and President Trump's threats of a blockade.
title: Watch: Video shows moment US forces 'apprehend' oil tanker

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Bollywood's 'Dhurandhar' continues its phenomenal box office journey, crossing Rs 500 crore net in its third week. Starring Ranveer Singh and Akshaye Khanna, the film is now the second-fastest to reach this milestone, surpassing 'Jawan'. With strong word-of-mouth and repeat viewership, its worldwide gross is nearing Rs 1,000 crore.
title: 'Dhurandhar' crosses Rs 500 crore in record time; eyes Rs 1,000 crore worldwide

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: IndiGo has issued a travel advisory warning of potential flight disruptions due to early-morning fog in Delhi and northern India on Sunday. Reduced visibility may cause delays or schedule changes, with operations teams monitoring weather to minimize inconvenience. Passengers are advised to check flight status and rebook or seek refunds if affected.
title: IndiGo alerts: Dense fog may disrupt flights across North India; travel advisory issued

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Veteran actor Mumtaz, who made her first television appearance in over five decades alongside Dharmendra on Indian Idol Season 13 in 2023, has revealed that she consciously avoids TV shows because she feels they don’t pay her what she deserves.
title: Mumtaz took Rs 18–20 lakh to appear with Dharmendra, rejected Seeta Aur Geeta due to low fee

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Airbus is reportedly planning to migrate sensitive workloads to a European cloud, moving away from Google and Microsoft services. This move is driven by concerns over digital sovereignty and the US CLOUD Act, which allows US authorities to access data held by American companies abroad. The aerospace giant aims to ensure European control over its critical data and operations.
title: Airbus plans cloud shift: Company moves away from AWS, Google, Microsoft

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: James Cameron's 'Avatar: Fire and Ash' has crossed Rs 50 crore in India within two days, showing strong family entertainer appeal. Despite a modest 15% growth on Saturday, its Rs 22.35 crore Day 2 collection lags significantly behind its predecessor.  The film's performance is being impacted by the continued success of 'Dhurandhar'.
title: 'Avatar: Fire and Ash' crosses Rs 50 crore mark; 'Dhurandhar' stays dominant

author: TNN
description: An Air India Express pilot allegedly assaulted a passenger at Delhi airport's Terminal 1 after a verbal altercation over queue jumping. The Ministry of Civil Aviation has ordered a probe and grounded the pilot, while the passenger claims he was pressured to not file a police complaint.
title: Delhi airport assault: Govt orders probe; passenger says forced to write letter

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: The Los Angeles Lakers, with a strong 19-7 record and recent offensive surge, face the struggling Los Angeles Clippers (6-21) tonight. The Lakers have been dominant since mid-November, especially with LeBron James healthy, while the Clippers are on an eight-game home losing streak. Luka Doncic led the Lakers to a season-high 143 points in their last outing.
title: Lakers vs Clippers (Dec 20): Preview, lineups, injury report and how to watch
